# What are the implications of the Polish missile attack for regional security in Europe and beyond?

## Summary
The missile attack near the rural village of Przewodow in Poland on Tuesday has had serious implications for regional security in Europe and beyond. <font color=#FF3399>[1]</font> Admiral Jim Stavridis, Former NATO Supreme Allied Commander, cautioned that not enough is known yet about the strike, but it could motivate NATO to reinforce air defense along the Ukraine-NATO border and provide Ukrainian MIG-29 aircraft from Poland, with US F-16s backfilling. <font color=#FF3399>[2]</font> In response to the deaths of two Polish citizens, repercussions from both NATO and the European Union are expected. <font color=#FF3399>[3]</font> Global leaders at the conference are attempting to prevent an escalation of the Kremlin's war on Ukraine, but the incident has raised awareness of the dangers of the Russian invasion of Ukraine and the potential for wider conflict. <font color=#FF3399>[4]</font> Ukraine has sent its own experts to investigate the incident and the Ukrainian president believes it was likely a Russian-made S-300 rocket that fell in Poland by accident. <font color=#FF3399>[5]</font> Thus, the missile attack has highlighted the potential risks posed by the conflict in the region and has sparked discussions on how best to ensure regional security.

